def: A narrow lane or alley. [Scot.] Jamieson.The narrow wynds, or alleys, on each side of the street. Bryant.
To form or deposit in strata, or layers, as substances in theearth; to arrange in strata.
One who slays; a killer; a murderer; a destrroyer of life.
One who stereotypes; one who makes stereotype plates, or worksin a stereotype foundry.
To tear up the roots of, or by the roots; hence, to tear from afoundation; to uproot.A piece of ground disrooted from its situation by subterraneousinundations. Goldsmith.
A style of interweaving giving to fabrics a channeled or flutedeffect; also, a fabric woven so as to have this effect; a rep.
Of or pertaining to the seal tribe; phocal.
A very small frond, or distinct portion of a compound frond.
